# This repository (llm-wiki) is checked out at the agent's working directory
# (/home/agent/work). Runtime state also lives here: source clones (sources/),
# the inner wiki content repo (wiki/, its own .git + remote), and harness junk.
# To make `git add -A` safe and never capture any of that, ignore EVERYTHING by
# default, then re-include only the definition + instance files this repo tracks.
#
# NOTE: this repo still TRACKS the wiki/ seed (index.md, log.md, pages/.gitkeep)
# so a fresh checkout materialises a usable wiki scaffold. .gitignore does not
# untrack files already in the index, so those seeds stay versioned here even
# though `wiki/` is not re-included below; the `/*` rule only hides *untracked*
# paths under wiki/ (new pages, the inner wiki/.git). On the agent volume,
# installation additionally runs `git update-index --skip-worktree` on the seed
# and instance files so their runtime changes never enter a definition commit.

/*

!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/INSTALLATION.md
!/CLAUDE.md
!/THIS-WIKI.md
!/wiki.config.json
!/skills/
!/scripts/

# Never track these even if a future allowlist entry would pull them in.
.DS_Store
node_modules/
